        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Is Fe³⁺ consistently more stable?\n\n**Yes — without exception in the data.** Across every matched ligand and stoichiometry examined, Fe³⁺ complexes show higher cumulative log β values than Fe²⁺ complexes:\n\n| Ligand | Complex | log β (Fe²⁺) | log β (Fe³⁺) | Δ log β |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1,2-diaminoethane (en) | ML | 4.34 | 6.23 | +1.89 |\n| 1,2-diaminoethane (en) | ML₂ | 7.65 | 11.07 | +3.42 |\n| 1,2-diaminoethane (en) | ML₃ | 9.73 | 14.67 | +4.94 |\n| 1,3-diaminopropane | ML | 4.55 | 5.98 | +1.43 |\n| 1,4-diaminobutane | ML | 4.04 | 5.48 | +1.44 |\n| 1,5-diaminopentane | ML | 3.83 | 5.25 | +1.42 |\n| diethylenetriamine (dien) | ML | 6.23 | 9.02 | +2.79 |\n| diethylenetriamine (dien) | ML₂ | 10.63 | 16.48 | +5.85 |\n| triethylenetetramine (trien) | ML | 7.76 | 10.00 | +2.24 |\n| tetraethylenepentamine | ML | 8.60 | 11.80 | +3.20 |\n| pentaethylenehexamine | ML | 9.00 | 12.80 | +3.80 |\n| N-methylethylenediamine | ML | 4.28 | 5.95 | +1.67 |\n| N,N,N′,N′-tetramethylethylenediamine | ML | 3.96 | 5.26 | +1.30 |",
